The paper proposes a new algorithm for implementing algorithmic fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the policy implications of their approach, which could fall under the sub-category of cyber law and ethics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of intersectionality, which could fall under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it relates to protecting the privacy and security of individuals who belong to multiple marginalized groups. Finally, the paper uses optimal transport theory, which could fall under the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
